summary:
The Security Council, recalling previous relevant resolutions and statements, and considering the reports of the Panel of Experts, determines that the proliferation of nuclear, chemical and biological weapons continues to threaten international peace and security. Acting under Article 41 of Chapter VII, it:

1. Extends the mandate of the Panel of Experts until 12 June 2011 and requests the Secretary-General to take necessary administrative measures;
2. Requests the Panel to provide a midterm report by 12 November 2010 and a final report thirty days prior to the termination of its mandate;
3. Urges all States, UN bodies, and interested parties to cooperate fully with the Committee and Panel of Experts, providing information on the implementation of measures imposed by resolutions 1718 (2006) and 1874 (2009);
4. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
